div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington.
In the Matter of the Application of Chung Him and Seid Yam for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
Filed in the United States District Court
In the Matter of the Application of Chung Him and Seid Yam for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
To the Clerk of the above entitled Court:

You will please prepare typewritten transcript of record in the above entitled cause on appeal, and file the same in the United States Circuit Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit, the said record to comprise the following papers:
1. Petition of the Appellees for writ of habeas corpus;
3. Return of order to show cause;
4. Order for writ of habeas corpus;
12. Admission of service of appellate papers;
13. Order directing the sending up of Department of Labor's files as part of the record.

We waive the provisions of the Act approved February 13, 1911, and direct that you forward typewritten transcript to the Circuit Court of Appeals for printing, as provided under rule 105 of this court.

I hereby acknowledge service of copy of the foregoing praecipe, waive the right to request the insertion of any other matters than those incorporated in the foregoing praecipe, and stipulate that the proceedings, papers, orders and documents included in said praecipe, constitute a full and sufficient and complete record upon appeal.
Attorneys for Chung Him and Seid Yam, Appellees.
